title: Tropical Cyclone Fina Batters Northern Territory | 10 News
description: Tropical Cyclone Fina has brought destructive winds and heavy rainfall, causing widespread damage across the Northern Territory capital.   The category 3 cyclone hit Darwin on Saturday, leaving more than 19,000 homes and businesses without power in the past 24 hours.  Darwin Airport was forced to close for 24 hours, only reopening this morning, and schools in Darwin are assessing whether it is safe for students to return tomorrow.  The Bureau of Meteorology says gusts of more than 200 km/h are possible, with the Northern Territory and parts of Western Australia still experiencing dangerous conditions as the system shifts away from the coast.  Authorities say communities should remain alert, as Cyclone Fina continues to evolve and warn it may bring further severe weather in the coming days. title: All Crew Evacuated After Fire on Cargo Ship at San Pedro Port, LA | 10 News
description: All crew members on board a cargo ship were forced to evacuate after it caught fire at the Port of San Pedro in Los Angeles on Friday night.  The Los Angeles Fire Department responded, sending 120 firefighters after the blaze triggered an explosion that disrupted power and crane operations onboard.  All 23 crew members were evacuated, and no injuries were reported.  Marine units continued to cool the ship’s exterior on Saturday, and no personnel were allowed below deck. title: Israel Airstrikes On Beirut Kill Hezbollah Military Leader | 10 News
description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu claims airstrikes on the Lebanese capital of Beirut have killed Hezbollah chief of staff, Ali Tabatabai.  The Israeli strikes came despite a US-brokered truce between Israel and Lebanon signed last year, with the Iran-backed Hezbollah yet to confirm the death of Tabatabai.  Lebanon's health ministry confirmed the strike, which hit a multi-storey building, killed five people and wounded 28 more.
